# LookingGlass Cyber Scout Query Splunk Technology Add-on

This software is distributed on an "AS IS" BASIS, WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.

## Welcome to the LookingGlass Cyber Scout Query Splunk Technology Add-on

#### The LookingGlass Cyber Scout Query Splunk Technology Add-on has been designed to collect data using a flexible query from ScoutPrime for use with Splunk.

#### Installation for a single server Splunk instance
Installing with Splunk Web for a single server Splunk instance
1) From the Splunk Web home screen, click the gear icon next to Apps.
2) Click Install app from file.
3) Locate Splunk_TA_lookingglasscyber_scout_query.tar.gz and click Upload
4) If Splunk Enterprise prompts you, click Yes to restart

Installing via CLI for a single server Splunk instance
1) Upload the Splunk_TA_lookingglasscyber_scout_query.tar.gz file to the Splunk instance
2) Extract the .tar.gz file in the apps directory of Splunk.  For example if your Splunk apps directory is located at /opt/splunk/etc/apps perform the following:
    a) sudo tar zxvf Splunk_TA_lookingglasscyber_scout_query.tar.gz -C /opt/splunk/etc/apps
3) Restart Splunk using /opt/splunk/bin/splunk restart

#### Installation for a distributed server Splunk environment
NOTE: The LookingGlass Cyber Scout Query Splunk Technology Add-on needs to be installed on a heavy forwarder in a distributed environment

Installing with Splunk Web for a distributed server Splunk environment
1) From the Splunk Web home screen on a heavy forwarder, click the gear icon next to Apps.
2) Click Install app from file.
3) Locate Splunk_TA_lookingglasscyber_scout_query.tar.gz and click Upload
4) If Splunk Enterprise prompts you, click Yes to restart

Installing via CLI for a distributed server Splunk environment
1) Upload the Splunk_TA_lookingglasscyber_scout_query.tar.gz file to a heavy forwarder
2) Extract the .tar.gz file in the apps directory of Splunk.  For example if your Splunk apps directory is located at /opt/splunk/etc/apps perform the following:
    a) sudo tar zxvf Splunk_TA_lookingglasscyber_scout_query.tar.gz -C /opt/splunk/etc/apps
3) Restart Splunk using /opt/splunk/bin/splunk restart

#### Configuration
Once the Splunk app has been installed, perform the following to configure the Technology Add-on:
1) From the Splunk Web home screen, click the gear icon next to Apps
2) From the list of Splunk apps and add-ons click on Set up under Actions for LookingGlass Cyber Scout Query
3) Ensure that Enable Scout Integration is checked
4) Enter in the fully qualified domain name of the ScoutPrime instance you are using in the LookingGlass Cyber Domain text area
5) Enter in the API token of the ScoutPrime user that you will be using to pull data from in the text box.
    a) If you need to get the ScoutPrime API key for the user, perform the following:
      i) Login to the ScoutPrime instance as the user whose API key you will be using
      ii) Click on the username in the upper right-hand corner
      iii) Click on API Tokens
      iv) Click on Show
    NOTE: If the user account does not have an API Token contact support@lookingglasscyber.com to have an API token created for the user.
6) Enter in the ScoutPrime query string in the text box for the data that you want to pull back.  Contact support@lookingglasscyber.com if you need assistance creating a ScoutPrime query.
7) (Optional - Recommendation is to keep the default)  Modify the time window to change the interval that data is pulled back over
8) (Optional - Recommendation is to keep the default)  Modify the time delay to change the interval that the query goes back before attempting to pull back data to ensure that data has been imported into ScoutPrime
9) (Optional) If the Splunk instance needs to use a proxy server to access the Internet ensure that Use a proxy server is checked
10) (Optional) Enter in the domain name and port information for the proxy server if the Splunk instance needs to use a proxy server to access the Internet
11) Click on Save in the lower right hand corner of the configuration screen when you are finished

